---
import Layout from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Layout title="About — Greg Maxfield" description="About Greg Maxfield — literary fiction author from the American West.">

<section class="about-section" style="padding-top:3rem;">
  <div class="container content-narrow">
    <div class="about-layout" style="gap:2.5rem;">
      <div class="about-photo">
        <img src="/images/greg-headshot.jpg" alt="Greg Maxfield" width="200" height="200" style="width:200px;height:200px;" />
      </div>
      <div class="about-text">
        <h1>About Greg</h1>
        <p>
          Greg Maxfield is a native of Emery County, Utah, where the desert teaches patience and the land
          holds memory. A native of the American West, he spent three decades in the energy industry before
          turning full-time to writing.
        </p>
        <p>
          He studied the history and geography of the American Southwest, has volunteered with Native American
          elders, and believes that place leaves something permanent in us — a mark we carry long after
          we've left. He lives in the Pacific Northwest and writes about the landscapes that shaped him.
        </p>
        <p>
          His work explores the intersections of family obligation, cultural memory, and moral reckoning
          in places where history isn't past — it's the ground you're standing on. His debut novel,
          <a href="/the-lund-covenant"><em>The Lund Covenant</em></a>, arrives in July 2026.
        </p>
        <h3 style="margin-top:2rem;">Elsewhere</h3>
        <p>
          Greg runs <a href="https://operationgrannyfiles.substack.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Operation Granny Files</a>,
          a family history project that turns genealogy into story, and builds productivity tools at
          <a href="https://conduital.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Conduital</a>. He serializes
          <em>The Lund Covenant</em> chapter by chapter on
          <a href="https://theunfoldingplot.substack.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Unfolding Plot</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</Layout>
